00:24:44,220 --> 00:24:48,220
 Kuzman napravio jedno prekrasno, kiparsko, bogato rješenje.

269
00:24:48,220 --> 00:24:58,220
 Inzistiraju na tome da taj Medo bude onako krupan i lijep kao što je on bio u njegovom rješenju koje je odabrala Komisija HNB.

270
00:24:58,220 --> 00:25:12,220
 Tu smo imali malo problema s obzirom da smo opet morali štediti pa smo od Royal Mint-a naručili relativno tanke pločice za kovanje i nije bilo previše prostora.

271
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:28,220
 Dobro, bez obzira na vremenski pritisak i sve nakon nekoliko iteracija uspeli smo naći jedno rješenje s kojim je bilo zadovoljan i autor, a koje je opet bilo izvedivo s obzirom na debljinu pločice za kovanje.

272
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:33,220
 In addition to coins, the Croatian Monetary Institute should have also printed banknotes.

273
00:25:33,220 --> 00:25:40,220
 But following analysis, it was concluded that this would be too large an investment, which would not have been justified at the time.

274
00:25:40,220 --> 00:25:43,220
 It was decided that the banknotes would be printed abroad.

275
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:47,220
 The banknotes were printed by the German printer Gizeke and Devrient.

276
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:59,220
 A group of experts was formed with Miroslav Šute, Vilko Žiljak, Đuro Črnjak and Nikola Raguš to ensure that the banknotes of the Republic of Croatia were produced and delivered in accordance with the contract.

277
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:06,220
 Vektorska grafika idealna bila i mi smo ju dignuli možda na ogromnu razinu.

278
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:10,220
 Mislim, danas ja mogu reći da je upravo čudo da je to tada uspjelo.

279
00:26:10,220 --> 00:26:18,220
 Međutim, imali smo na raspolaganju fotojedinice, visokih rezolucija, ogromnih što se tiče tog vremena.

280
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:22,220
 Zatim smo imali izvanredne programe.

281
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:37,220
 Napravili smo jenom prekrasnu malu grupu ljudi koja je bila apsolutno posvećena tom poslu koja nije pitala niti za radno vrijeme niti plaće su tada isto bile usklađene kao što su bile i ostale.

282
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:39,220
 Dakle, ni ništa pretjerano.

283
00:26:39,220 --> 00:26:45,220
 The only serious problem related to our banknotes appeared shortly after their introduction.

284
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:52,220
 In Germany, the Bundesbank warned of the excessive similarity between the ten kuna and the ten german mark note,

285
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:54,220
 which could lead to confusion.

286
00:26:55,220 --> 00:27:13,220
 Istražili smo i doista se pokazalo da Hrvati, odnosno ljudi koji su tamo radili su koristili naših deset kuna koje su, da tako kažem, podvaljivali kao deset maraka.

287
00:27:13,220 --> 00:27:41,220
 To je postalo intenzivno i mi smo zamoljeni od Bundesbanker da razmutrimo mogućnost kako bi se izbjegla kakva zabuna da tu novčanicu zamijenimo novom serijom koja bi bila vidno prvenstveno bojom drugačija od tih deset maraka koje, eto, prije dvije godine u odnosu na naša izdanja Bundesbanker stavila vopice.

